00:37:55.565 --> 00:37:57.275
But I'm ready for more than that now.

745
00:37:57.776 --> 00:37:58.818
No. you're not.

746
00:37:58.985 --> 00:38:01.305
That's not what you thought
when I took on captain america.

747
00:38:01.446 --> 00:38:04.073
Trust me. kid. If cap wanted
to lay you out. he would've.

748
00:38:04.491 --> 00:38:07.702
Listen to me. If you come across
these weapons again. call happy.

749
00:38:07.869 --> 00:38:09.162
[Car engine revs over speaker]

750
00:38:09.329 --> 00:38:10.622
Are you driving?

751
00:38:10.789 --> 00:38:13.792
You know. it's never too early
to start thinking about college.

752
00:38:13.958 --> 00:38:15.710
I got some pull at mit. End call.

753
00:38:17.295 --> 00:38:18.588
No. I don't need to go to...

754
00:38:18.755 --> 00:38:20.799
Friday:
Mr. Stark is no longer connected.

755
00:38:23.510 --> 00:38:25.345
That's awesome.

756
00:38:27.972 --> 00:38:31.434
"Stay close to the ground"?
What is he talking about?

757
00:38:33.102 --> 00:38:35.104
[Mu]

758
00:38:36.439 --> 00:38:39.442
[Low humming]

759
00:38:43.905 --> 00:38:45.031
[Weapon humming]

760
00:38:45.698 --> 00:38:48.034
[Yodeling ringtone plays]

761
00:38:50.537 --> 00:38:52.163
Hey. what's up? I'm on my way back.

762
00:38:52.330 --> 00:38:55.542
Actually. I was calling to say
maybe you shouldn't come. Listen.

763
00:38:55.708 --> 00:38:57.919
Flash:
When I say "penis." you say "Parker."

764
00:38:58.086 --> 00:38:59.087
-Penis! All: Parker!

765
00:38:59.254 --> 00:39:00.463
- Penis!
- Parker!

766
00:39:00.964 --> 00:39:03.174
Ned:
Sorry. Peter. I guess we're still losers.

767
00:39:03.341 --> 00:39:06.302
- I'll see you tomorrow.
- I'll see you tomorrow in school.

768
00:39:08.137 --> 00:39:10.056
[Mu]

769
00:39:18.731 --> 00:39:21.150
[Rock music playing]

770
00:39:21.317 --> 00:39:23.319
[Machines and tools
whirring and beeping]

771
00:39:34.706 --> 00:39:35.707
Whoa. whoa.

772
00:39:44.090 --> 00:39:46.092
[Mu]

773
00:39:46.342 --> 00:39:48.052
Idiots.

774
00:39:48.887 --> 00:39:50.013
Idiots.

775
00:39:52.557 --> 00:39:53.600
Mason: Boss?

776
00:39:53.933 --> 00:39:57.228
Your wife keeps texting you.
Something about a brake light.

777
00:39:57.645 --> 00:39:59.814
What'd I tell you about
looking at my phone?

778
00:39:59.981 --> 00:40:01.232
Oh. Sorry. You left it out.

779
00:40:01.399 --> 00:40:03.234
You know
I'm a curious person by nature.

780
00:40:05.278 --> 00:40:08.281
I finished designing
that high-altitude vacuum seal.

781
00:40:08.489 --> 00:40:09.490
Huh?

782
00:40:09.657 --> 00:40:12.535
In case you want to.
you know. go for the big one?

783
00:40:12.702 --> 00:40:14.746
You're still on that? I told you. no.

784
00:40:14.913 --> 00:40:16.456
The answer's no. Forget it.

785
00:40:16.664 --> 00:40:18.875
[Van sputtering]

786
00:40:28.134 --> 00:40:30.595
I mean. that was badass. Ha.

787
00:40:33.222 --> 00:40:37.101
How many times have I told you
not to fire them out in the open?

788
00:40:37.268 --> 00:40:39.812
- You said. move the merchandise.
- Under the radar.

789
00:40:39.979 --> 00:40:41.189
Under the radar!

790
00:40:41.356 --> 00:40:43.107
That's how we survive.

791
00:40:43.274 --> 00:40:46.611
If you bring damage control or
the avengers down here. we're through.

792
00:40:47.236 --> 00:40:50.198
You're out there wearing that goofy thing.
lighting up cars...

793
00:40:50.365 --> 00:40:51.866
Calling yourself the shocker.

794
00:40:52.033 --> 00:40:55.161
"I'm the shocker. I shock people."
What is this. pro wrestling?

795
00:40:55.328 --> 00:40:57.121
Ah. whatever. old man. Come on.

796
00:41:01.751 --> 00:41:04.420
I know you don't give a crap
about anything.

797
00:41:06.381 --> 00:41:09.509
I built this whole place
because I got people I have to look after.

798
00:41:09.676 --> 00:41:12.887
Yeah. yeah. yeah.

799
00:41:15.139 --> 00:41:16.557
You know what?

800
00:41:16.724 --> 00:41:19.394
I can't afford your bullshit.

801
00:41:19.560 --> 00:41:21.020
- Get out of here.
- What?

802
00:41:21.187 --> 00:41:24.482
- You're done. You're off the crew.
- Yeah. all right.

803
00:41:25.358 --> 00:41:26.401
All right. Heh.

804
00:41:26.567 --> 00:41:28.987
Wonder if you can afford me
out there. though. right?

805
00:41:29.153 --> 00:41:30.989
With everything I know.

806
00:41:31.948 --> 00:41:34.784
- Excuse me?
- Uh. I'm just saying...

807
00:41:35.118 --> 00:41:38.788
Maybe your wife would like to know
where you really get your money from.

808
00:41:39.580 --> 00:41:41.207
- You know what?
- What?

809
00:41:41.582 --> 00:41:42.750
You're right.

810
00:41:42.917 --> 00:41:44.377
- That work?
- I don't know.

811
00:41:45.670 --> 00:41:47.213
I can't afford that.

812
00:41:47.422 --> 00:41:49.924
Whoa. whoa. whoa. Wait.

813
00:41:54.303 --> 00:41:56.389
[Weapon powers down]

814
00:41:56.556 --> 00:41:58.057
Damn.

815
00:42:00.643 --> 00:42:03.021
- I thought this was the antigravity gun.
- What?

816
00:42:03.187 --> 00:42:04.272
No. that's that one.

817
00:42:06.149 --> 00:42:08.151
[Mu]

818
00:42:17.744 --> 00:42:18.786
Here.

819
00:42:20.079 --> 00:42:23.958
Now you're the shocker. Go out there
and find that weapon he lost.

820
00:42:24.125 --> 00:42:25.168
All right.

821
00:42:34.594 --> 00:42:36.387
Ned:
Hey. thanks for bailing on me.

822
00:42:36.554 --> 00:42:38.514
Yeah. well. something came up.

823
00:42:38.681 --> 00:42:39.891
What is that?

824
00:42:40.308 --> 00:42:42.852
I don't know.
Some guy tried to vaporize me with it.

825
00:42:43.019 --> 00:42:44.479
- Seriously?
- Yeah.

826
00:42:44.645 --> 00:42:46.105
Awesome.

827
00:42:46.272 --> 00:42:49.358
I mean. not awesome.
Heh. totally uncool of that guy.

828
00:42:49.525 --> 00:42:51.319
So scary.

829
00:42:52.653 --> 00:42:54.322
Well. look. I think it's...

830
00:42:54.489 --> 00:42:55.948
A power source.

831
00:42:56.115 --> 00:42:58.701
Yeah. but it's connected
to all these microprocessors.

832
00:42:58.868 --> 00:43:02.080
That's an inductive charging plate.
That's what I use to charge my toothbrush.

833
00:43:02.246 --> 00:43:05.291
Whoever's making these weapons
is combining alien tech with ours.

834
00:43:05.458 --> 00:43:09.337
That is literally the coolest sentence
anyone has ever said.

835
00:43:09.504 --> 00:43:12.548
I just want to thank you
for letting me be part of your journey...

836
00:43:12.715 --> 00:43:15.093
Into this amazing...

837
00:43:17.678 --> 00:43:20.723
Keep your fingers clear of the blades.

838
00:43:22.850 --> 00:43:24.977
I gotta figure out what this is
and who makes it.

839
00:43:25.144 --> 00:43:27.355
Ned: We'll go to the lab after class
and run tests.

840
00:43:27.522 --> 00:43:28.815
Let's do it.

841
00:43:31.651 --> 00:43:33.653
[Mu]

842
00:43:36.280 --> 00:43:38.574
First. we put the glowy thing
in the mass spectrometer.

843
00:43:38.741 --> 00:43:41.202
We gotta come up with a better name
than "glowy thingy."

844
00:43:41.369 --> 00:43:42.453
You're right.

845
00:43:43.955 --> 00:43:45.081
Crap.

846
00:43:45.706 --> 00:43:47.917
[Whispering]
Come on. come on. come on.

847
00:43:51.838 --> 00:43:53.381
High schools creep me out.

848
00:43:54.090 --> 00:43:56.050
They got this funny smell. you know?

849
00:43:56.217 --> 00:43:58.511
Hey. that's one of the guys
that tried to kill me.

850
00:43:58.678 --> 00:43:59.720
[Whispering] What?

851
00:43:59.887 --> 00:44:01.389
- Yeah.
- We gotta get out of here.

852
00:44:01.556 --> 00:44:03.432
No. no. no. I gotta follow them.

853
00:44:03.599 --> 00:44:06.185
They can lead me to the guy
that dropped me in the lake.

854
00:44:06.352 --> 00:44:08.604
- Someone dropped you in a lake?
- Yeah. it was not good.

855
00:44:10.606 --> 00:44:12.024
-Peter—- -no. Stay there. ned.

856
00:44:12.191 --> 00:44:13.776
Peter.

857
00:44:14.277 --> 00:44:16.362
[Mu]

858
00:44:16.779 --> 00:44:18.072
What are you doing?

859
00:44:18.239 --> 00:44:19.479
[In normal voice] Nothing. Heh.

860
00:44:19.574 --> 00:44:21.826
- Oh.
- Yeah. You good?

861
00:44:23.244 --> 00:44:25.788
[Mu]

862
00:44:25.997 --> 00:44:29.417
Randy: Can you imagine what the boss
would say if he knew where we were?

863
00:44:29.584 --> 00:44:31.669
It's saying there was
an energy pulse here.

864
00:44:31.836 --> 00:44:33.296
Randy:
There's no sign of the weapon.

865
00:44:33.462 --> 00:44:36.382
- And even if it was here. now it's gone.
- So are we.

866
00:44:42.096 --> 00:44:44.098
[Mu]

867
00:45:08.998 --> 00:45:11.918
This is so awesome.

868
00:45:12.084 --> 00:45:13.920
I know. right?

869
00:45:17.131 --> 00:45:18.925
They're in Brooklyn.

870
00:45:23.095 --> 00:45:25.056
Staten island.

871
00:45:28.017 --> 00:45:30.603
[Clanking and whirring]

872
00:45:30.770 --> 00:45:32.688
Leaving Jersey.

873
00:45:34.732 --> 00:45:36.734
[Mu]

874
00:45:36.901 --> 00:45:38.903
[Beeping]

875
00:45:40.279 --> 00:45:41.906
They stopped.

876
00:45:44.659 --> 00:45:45.743
Maryland?

877
00:45:45.910 --> 00:45:48.162
- What's there?
- I don't know.

878
00:45:48.329 --> 00:45:49.372
Evil lair? Heh.

879
00:45:49.914 --> 00:45:51.958
- They have a lair?
- A gang with alien guns...

880
00:45:52.124 --> 00:45:53.918
Run by a guy with wings? Yeah.

881
00:45:54.085 --> 00:45:55.503
Badass.

882
00:45:55.670 --> 00:45:58.547
But how are you gonna get there
if it's. like. 300 miles away?

883
00:46:00.800 --> 00:46:03.386
It's not too far from DC.

884
00:46:04.470 --> 00:46:05.596
- Hey. it's Peter.
- Guys.

885
00:46:05.763 --> 00:46:06.806
- Peter?
- Hey. buddy.

886
00:46:06.973 --> 00:46:08.849
I was hoping I could rejoin the team.

887
00:46:09.016 --> 00:46:10.643
No. no way. You can't quit on us...

888
00:46:10.810 --> 00:46:13.437
Stroll up and be welcomed back
by everyone.

889
00:46:13.604 --> 00:46:16.482
Hey. welcome back!
Flash. you're back to first alternate.

890
00:46:16.649 --> 00:46:17.984
- What?
- He's taking your place.

891
00:46:18.150 --> 00:46:19.527
Excuse me. can we go already?

892
00:46:19.694 --> 00:46:23.489
I was hoping to get in some protesting
in front of an embassy before dinner.

893
00:46:23.656 --> 00:46:26.117
Protesting is patriotic.
Let's get on the bus.

894
00:46:26.325 --> 00:46:27.910
[Mu]

895
00:46:28.077 --> 00:46:31.664
Liz: Focus up.
Our next topic is the moons of saturn.

896
00:46:31.831 --> 00:46:33.457
The second law of thermodynamics.

897
00:46:34.000 --> 00:46:35.918
- Frank Sinatra.
- Fort sumter.

898
00:46:36.627 --> 00:46:38.921
- Flash is wrong.
- Okay. let's focus. Next one.

899
00:46:39.088 --> 00:46:40.423
Liz. don't ovennork them.

900
00:46:40.923 --> 00:46:42.633
Uh. strontium. barium. vibranium.

901
00:46:42.800 --> 00:46:45.511
- Very good. Peter. Glad to have you back.
- Glad to be back.

902
00:46:45.678 --> 00:46:46.971
[Phone buzzing]

903
00:46:47.138 --> 00:46:50.141
- What is the current standard unit of...?
- Can I take this real quick?

904
00:46:50.308 --> 00:46:51.809
Yeah. fine.

905
00:46:51.976 --> 00:46:53.769
- Hello?
- Got a blip on my screen here.

906
00:46:53.936 --> 00:46:54.979
You left New York?

907
00:46:55.146 --> 00:46:57.066
- Liz: Okay. focus up. everyone.
- Tracker. Uh...

908
00:46:57.148 --> 00:46:59.068
Yeah. it's just a school trip.
It's. uh. nothing.

909
00:46:59.233 --> 00:47:01.652
Happy. I gotta say.
tracking me without permission...

910
00:47:01.819 --> 00:47:03.612
Is a complete violation of privacy.

911
00:47:04.405 --> 00:47:06.115
- That's different.
- What's different?

912
00:47:06.282 --> 00:47:08.743
Nothing. Look. it's just
the academic decathlon.

913
00:47:08.909 --> 00:47:11.996
- It's no big deal.
- Hey. hey. I'll decide if it's no big deal.

914
00:47:14.165 --> 00:47:16.751
Sounds like no big deal.
but remember. I'm watching you.

915
00:47:16.959 --> 00:47:18.961
[Mu]

916
00:47:28.054 --> 00:47:30.723
- Everyone stick together.
- Yeah.

917
00:47:31.223 --> 00:47:33.059
Charles:
You kidding me? This place is huge.

918
00:47:33.225 --> 00:47:35.811
- Flash: I've seen bigger.
- There's a bird in here.

919
00:47:35.978 --> 00:47:39.231
- Hey. you brought your laptop. right?
- Why?

920
00:47:40.649 --> 00:47:42.151
[Mu]

921
00:47:44.070 --> 00:47:47.073
[Whirs then chirping]

922
00:47:47.281 --> 00:47:48.657
Peter...

923
00:47:48.824 --> 00:47:51.827
Why are we removing
the tracker from your suit?

924
00:47:53.371 --> 00:47:56.499
I gotta follow these guys to their boss
before they move again...

925
00:47:56.665 --> 00:47:59.585
And I don't really want Mr. Stark
to know about it.

926
00:47:59.752 --> 00:48:01.587
So you're lying to iron man now?

927
00:48:01.754 --> 00:48:03.381
No. I'm not lying.

928
00:48:03.547 --> 00:48:06.175
He just doesn't really get
what I can do yet.

929
00:48:07.802 --> 00:48:09.220
Peter: Ah...

930
00:48:10.763 --> 00:48:12.264
Gotcha.

931
00:48:12.431 --> 00:48:16.602
All right. happy. enjoy tracking this lamp.

932
00:48:19.563 --> 00:48:21.982
There's a ton
of other subsystems in here...

933
00:48:22.149 --> 00:48:24.026
- Hmm?
- But they're all disabled...

934
00:48:24.193 --> 00:48:26.404
By the training wheels protocol.

935
00:48:26.570 --> 00:48:27.696
What?

936
00:48:27.863 --> 00:48:31.492
"Training wheels protocol"? Turn it off.

937
00:48:31.659 --> 00:48:34.578
I don't think that's a good idea.
They're blocked for a reason.

938
00:48:34.995 --> 00:48:37.331
Come on. man.
I don't need training wheels.

939
00:48:37.498 --> 00:48:39.875
I'm sick of him treating me
like a kid all the time.

940
00:48:40.042 --> 00:48:42.336
- It's not cool.
- But you are a kid.

941
00:48:42.503 --> 00:48:44.588
A kid who can stop a bus
with his bare hands.

942
00:48:44.755 --> 00:48:48.509
Peter. I just don't think this is a great
idea. I mean. what if this is illegal?

943
00:48:48.676 --> 00:48:51.637
Look. please.
This is my chance to prove myself.

944
00:48:51.804 --> 00:48:53.556
I can handle it. Ned. come on.

945
00:48:53.722 --> 00:48:56.434
- I don't think this is a good idea.
- The guy in the chair.

946
00:48:56.892 --> 00:48:59.061
- Don't do that.
- Come on.

947
00:48:59.270 --> 00:49:00.855
[Sighs]

948
00:49:02.690 --> 00:49:05.818
[Suit whirs and crackles]

949
00:49:06.026 --> 00:49:08.028
[Mu]

950
00:49:13.159 --> 00:49:15.077
The glowy thing. it's evidence.
Keep it safe.

951
00:49:15.244 --> 00:49:16.829
- All right?
- Okay. Okay.

952
00:49:18.456 --> 00:49:19.999
- They're moving.
- Be careful.

953
00:49:24.044 --> 00:49:25.754
- Hey. Liz.
- [Whispering] Perfect timing.

954
00:49:26.172 --> 00:49:27.298
We're gonna go swimming.

955
00:49:27.465 --> 00:49:29.385
- Come on. come on. come on.
- [Whispering] What?

956
00:49:29.800 --> 00:49:31.552
- Hey. Peter.
- Hi.

957
00:49:33.220 --> 00:49:34.555
Hey.

958
00:49:35.181 --> 00:49:39.018
[In normal voice] I was. uh... I was
gonna go study in the business center.

959
00:49:39.185 --> 00:49:42.145
[In normal voice] You don't need to.
You're the smartest guy I've ever met.

960
00:49:43.147 --> 00:49:46.942
Um. a rebellious group activity the day
before competition is good for morale.

961
00:49:48.277 --> 00:49:50.488
Um. well. I read that in a Ted talk. so...

962
00:49:53.073 --> 00:49:54.992
And I read a coaching book.

963
00:49:56.076 --> 00:49:58.162
Wow. you really...
This is really important to you.

964
00:49:58.329 --> 00:50:00.206
Yeah. It's our future.

965
00:50:00.372 --> 00:50:01.790
I'm not gonna screw it up.

966
00:50:02.833 --> 00:50:06.712
Besides. we raided the minibar
and these candy bars were. like. $11.

967
00:50:06.879 --> 00:50:10.132
- So get your trunks on and come on.
- Charles: Come on.

968
00:50:10.299 --> 00:50:12.426
Sally: Come on.
Liz: I'm coming. I'm coming.

969
00:50:12.593 --> 00:50:13.636
Cindy: Let's go.

970
00:50:17.640 --> 00:50:20.726
[Mu]

971
00:50:27.316 --> 00:50:28.734
[Sighs]

972
00:50:37.535 --> 00:50:39.787
- Spider suit: Good evening. Peter.
- Hello? Hello?

973
00:50:39.954 --> 00:50:42.873
Congratulations on completing
the training wheels protocol...

974
00:50:43.040 --> 00:50:45.584
And gaining access
to your suit's full capabilities.

975
00:50:45.751 --> 00:50:47.336
Ah. thank you.

976
00:50:47.503 --> 00:50:49.338
Where would you like
to take me tonight?

977
00:50:49.505 --> 00:50:52.216
I put a tracker on someone.
He's a bad guy.

978
00:50:52.383 --> 00:50:54.426
Tracker located.

979
00:50:54.885 --> 00:50:57.137
Plotting course to intercept target.

980
00:50:57.304 --> 00:51:00.391
As long as I make it back
in time for decathlon. it's fine.

981
00:51:01.642 --> 00:51:03.644
[Mu]

982
00:51:04.436 --> 00:51:06.438
[Mu]

983
00:51:08.399 --> 00:51:11.110
Spider suit: One hundred meters
from destination and closing.

984
00:51:11.485 --> 00:51:13.112
Jump now.

985
00:51:17.616 --> 00:51:19.618
Detecting three individuals.

986
00:51:20.369 --> 00:51:23.998
Peter [whispering]: Why is their secret
lair in a gas station? That's so lame.

987
00:51:25.791 --> 00:51:27.167
[Mu]

988
00:51:28.002 --> 00:51:29.896
[In normal voice]
Hey. suit lady. what are they doing?

989
00:51:29.920 --> 00:51:31.356
Do you want to hear
what they're saying?

990
00:51:31.380 --> 00:51:33.841
I can hear what they're saying? Uh. yeah.

991
00:51:34.008 --> 00:51:35.926
Activating enhanced
reconnaissance mode.

992
00:51:36.093 --> 00:51:38.013
Mason:
I got the gauntlet from the Lagos cleanup.

993
00:51:38.053 --> 00:51:39.054
The rest is my design.

994
00:51:39.221 --> 00:51:40.514
Whoa. that's so cool.

995
00:51:40.681 --> 00:51:41.825
Randy:
Can't believe they're still cleaning up...

996
00:51:41.849 --> 00:51:43.493
That triskelion mess.
Schultz: I love it.

997
00:51:43.517 --> 00:51:46.103
They keep making messes.
we keep getting rich.

998
00:51:46.270 --> 00:51:47.271
Mason: Target inbound.

999
00:51:47.438 --> 00:51:49.165
[Whispering]
Whoa. they're in the middle of a heist.

1000
00:51:49.189 --> 00:51:51.358
I could catch them red-handed.
This is awesome.

1001
00:51:51.525 --> 00:51:53.962
[In normal voice] Okay.
I'll get closer to see what's happening.

1002
00:51:53.986 --> 00:51:56.697
Would you like me to engage
enhanced combat mode?

1003
00:51:56.864 --> 00:51:59.199
Uh. "enhanced combat mode"? Yeah.

1004
00:51:59.366 --> 00:52:00.826
Activating instant kill.

1005
00:52:00.993 --> 00:52:03.078
No. no. no. I don't want to kill anybody.

1006
00:52:03.245 --> 00:52:05.539
Deactivating instant kill.

1007
00:52:05.748 --> 00:52:06.790
[Mu]

1008
00:52:06.957 --> 00:52:08.334
[Grunts]

1009
00:52:08.500 --> 00:52:10.252
Did you hear that?

1010
00:52:10.669 --> 00:52:12.671
What the hell just happened?
What was that?

1011
00:52:12.838 --> 00:52:15.257
You jumped off the sign
and landed on your face.

1012
00:52:17.801 --> 00:52:19.161
What's wrong with my web-shooters?

1013
00:52:19.261 --> 00:52:21.597
Rapid-fire is the default
for enhanced combat mode.

1014
00:52:21.764 --> 00:52:24.475
- Why would I need rapid-fire?
- Would you like to see more options?

1015
00:52:24.642 --> 00:52:27.645
You have 576 possible
web-shooter combinations.

1016
00:52:27.853 --> 00:52:29.521
Whoa. Mr. Stark really overdid it.

1017
00:52:29.688 --> 00:52:30.856
You two wait right here.

1018
00:52:31.023 --> 00:52:33.150
Wait. You're gonna want
to turn on the dampers.

1019
00:52:33.317 --> 00:52:36.612
- That thing will shatter your arm.
- All right. where's the dampers?

1020
00:52:36.779 --> 00:52:38.489
- Peter: That one.
- Great choice.

1021
00:52:38.864 --> 00:52:41.241
Would you like me to set this
as your new default?

1022
00:52:42.660 --> 00:52:43.786
No. no. no.

1023
00:52:43.952 --> 00:52:46.497
- Push that in. No. the other...
- Here? This one here?

1024
00:52:46.664 --> 00:52:48.999
- What was that?
- Taser webs.

1025
00:52:49.166 --> 00:52:51.001
Taser webs? I don't want taser webs.

1026
00:52:51.168 --> 00:52:53.671
You seem to be unfamiliar
with your web-shooter settings.

1027
00:52:54.171 --> 00:52:55.881
Would you like to run
a refresher course?

1028
00:52:56.048 --> 00:52:58.384
- No. Just... you choose.
- Sure thing.

1029
00:52:58.550 --> 00:53:01.220
Woman [over radio]:
Six-Alpha-niner. are you running on time?

1030
00:53:01.387 --> 00:53:04.848
Copy. central.
Six-Alpha-niner on schedule.

1031
00:53:05.057 --> 00:53:06.767
[Mu]

1032
00:53:07.559 --> 00:53:09.679
- Schultz: I got a visual.
- Green light. green light.

1033
00:53:14.108 --> 00:53:15.401
Oh. that's him.

1034
00:53:19.154 --> 00:53:21.198
Okay. I got eyes on the convoy.

1035
00:53:21.365 --> 00:53:22.783
Pulling in behind the caboose.

1036
00:53:24.576 --> 00:53:26.370
Mason [over radio]:
Deploy anchors.

1037
00:53:27.913 --> 00:53:29.915
[Mu]

1038
00:53:36.422 --> 00:53:37.756
Dropping down.

1039
00:53:40.342 --> 00:53:42.261
No outgoing distress signals.
You're clear.

1040
00:53:44.221 --> 00:53:47.516
Hey. Looks like they got
some good stuff here.

1041
00:53:55.065 --> 00:53:58.819
Whoa. cool. It's like some kind of
matter phase shifter.

1042
00:54:03.449 --> 00:54:05.367
All right. coming up.

1043
00:54:10.706 --> 00:54:12.833
Hey. big bird. This doesn't belong to you.

1044
00:54:14.126 --> 00:54:15.627
Oh. god.

1045
00:54:22.426 --> 00:54:25.026
- Suit lady. what was that?!
- Spider suit: You told me to choose.

1046
00:54:25.929 --> 00:54:28.474
What? No. just set everything
back to normal.

1047
00:54:28.974 --> 00:54:30.893
Activating all systems.

1048
00:54:40.235 --> 00:54:42.237
[Whirring and rumbling]

1049
00:54:47.493 --> 00:54:48.827
My head.

1050
00:54:48.994 --> 00:54:51.872
Spider suit:
You appear to have a mild concussion.

1051
00:54:53.999 --> 00:54:57.169
Hey. so where am I right now?

1052
00:54:57.336 --> 00:54:58.462
I'm not sure.

1053
00:54:59.004 --> 00:55:01.173
The container walls are hindering
my sensors.

1054
00:55:01.381 --> 00:55:02.716
[Mu]

1055
00:55:02.883 --> 00:55:04.218
Wait a minute.

1056
00:55:04.384 --> 00:55:07.930
They must have hijacked the truck
and taken me to their evil lair.

1057
00:55:08.430 --> 00:55:11.850
Okay. suit lady. we're gonna
have to fight our way out of this one.

1058
00:55:12.226 --> 00:55:14.269
Three. two. one.

1059
00:55:17.397 --> 00:55:19.274
[Panting]

1060
00:55:20.818 --> 00:55:22.528
What is this place?

1061
00:55:22.694 --> 00:55:23.946
Suit lady. where am I?

1062
00:55:24.112 --> 00:55:27.032
You're in the most secure facility
on the eastern seaboard.

1063
00:55:27.199 --> 00:55:28.784
The damage control
deep-storage vault.

1064
00:55:28.951 --> 00:55:32.162
No. Seriously? Argh!

1065
00:55:32.371 --> 00:55:34.331
[Grunting]

1066
00:55:34.498 --> 00:55:36.792
The door will most likely
remain closed until morning.

1067
00:55:36.959 --> 00:55:38.252
Morning?

1068
00:55:38.418 --> 00:55:43.507
Hey. suit lady. I kind of feel bad
calling you "suit lady." you know?

1069
00:55:43.674 --> 00:55:45.968
I think I should probably give you a name.

1070
00:55:46.134 --> 00:55:48.470
Like Liz. No. no. no.

1071
00:55:48.637 --> 00:55:50.639
God. that's... that's weird.

1072
00:55:50.806 --> 00:55:53.183
What about Karen?

1073
00:55:53.600 --> 00:55:55.578
Spider suit: You can call me Karen
if you would like.

1074
00:55:55.602 --> 00:55:58.730
Hey. Karen. what else can this suit do?

1075
00:55:59.189 --> 00:56:00.816
[Gasps] What?

1076
00:56:00.983 --> 00:56:02.901
Maybe we should run
that refresher course.

1077
00:56:03.068 --> 00:56:04.653
- Karen: Ricochet web.
- Ricochet web.

1078
00:56:04.820 --> 00:56:08.282
- Whoa. Cool.
- Splitter web.

1079
00:56:09.449 --> 00:56:12.327
- Web grenade.
- Web grenade!

1080
00:56:14.079 --> 00:56:16.748
Should I tell Liz that I'm spider-man?

1081
00:56:16.915 --> 00:56:18.000
Who is Liz?

1082
00:56:18.166 --> 00:56:20.794
Who's Liz? Heh. She's... heh. heh.

1083
00:56:20.961 --> 00:56:22.421
She's the best. She's awesome.

1084
00:56:22.588 --> 00:56:25.299
She's just a girl who goes to my school.

1085
00:56:25.465 --> 00:56:26.508
And. uh...

1086
00:56:26.675 --> 00:56:30.596
Yeah. I just... I really want to tell her.
but it's kind of weird. you know?

1087
00:56:30.762 --> 00:56:33.974
"Hey. I'm spider-man."

1088
00:56:34.141 --> 00:56:35.267
What's weird about that?

1089
00:56:35.434 --> 00:56:37.477
What if she's expecting
someone like Tony stark?

1090
00:56:37.644 --> 00:56:39.646
Imagine how disappointed
she'd be when she sees me.

1091
00:56:39.813 --> 00:56:43.358
Well. if I were her.
I wouldn't be disappointed at all.

1092
00:56:43.525 --> 00:56:45.027
Thanks. Karen.

1093
00:56:45.193 --> 00:56:47.946
It's really nice
to have somebody to talk to.

1094
00:56:48.113 --> 00:56:49.948
Hey. how long we been here anyways?

1095
00:56:50.115 --> 00:56:51.992
- Thirty-seven minutes.
- What?!

1096
00:56:52.159 --> 00:56:53.869
Thirty-seven minutes? That's insane.

1097
00:56:54.036 --> 00:56:57.706
I cannot take this anymore.
I got to... I gotta get out of here.

1098
00:56:59.625 --> 00:57:02.461
There's got to be something in here
I can use.

1099
00:57:03.503 --> 00:57:05.255
Okay. let's see.

1100
00:57:05.422 --> 00:57:06.965
Nope.

1101
00:57:08.175 --> 00:57:09.343
That's awesome.

1102
00:57:11.219 --> 00:57:12.459
Hey. it's like the glowy thing.

1103
00:57:12.596 --> 00:57:15.599
That glowy thing is
an explosive chitauri energy core.

1104
00:57:15.766 --> 00:57:17.768
You mean. we've been
carrying around a bomb?

1105
00:57:17.935 --> 00:57:21.647
It would require radiation
to transform it into an explosive state.

1106
00:57:21.813 --> 00:57:22.856
[Beeps]

1107
00:57:23.065 --> 00:57:24.483
No. no. no.

1108
00:57:25.150 --> 00:57:26.360
[Panting]

1109
00:57:27.152 --> 00:57:28.195
[Grunts]

1110
00:57:28.362 --> 00:57:31.239
Hey! Please!
Please. somebody let me out! Hey!

1111
00:57:31.406 --> 00:57:33.406
Karen. you have to help me override
that time lock.

1112
00:57:34.076 --> 00:57:36.078
Okay. Karen. lower the voltage and run it.

1113
00:57:36.244 --> 00:57:37.746
Trial unsuccessful.

1114
00:57:37.913 --> 00:57:39.349
Okay. we're just gonna have
to try every sequence.

1115
00:57:39.373 --> 00:57:41.166
[Mu]

1116
00:57:43.168 --> 00:57:46.296
Liz: Ned. Peter. we're gonna be late.
Come on. let's go.

1117
00:57:46.463 --> 00:57:48.674
Okay. Uh. hold on. hold on.

1118
00:57:49.591 --> 00:57:51.134
[Groans]

1119
00:57:52.552 --> 00:57:55.639
Initiating trial 247.

1120
00:57:56.181 --> 00:57:57.557
It worked. It works.

1121
00:58:02.854 --> 00:58:04.856
[Mu]

1122
00:58:10.028 --> 00:58:13.615
Please be sure
all cell phones are turned off.

1123
00:58:13.782 --> 00:58:14.825
Thank you.

1124
00:58:14.992 --> 00:58:17.011
Peter: Karen. get me to
decathlon as fast as possible.

1125
00:58:17.035 --> 00:58:18.304
Kare n:
Sure thing. Just tell me where it is.

1126
00:58:18.328 --> 00:58:20.098
Across the street
from the Washington monument.

1127
00:58:20.122 --> 00:58:21.265
Ned [on recording]:
It's ned. Leave a message.

1128
00:58:21.289 --> 00:58:23.125
Call me back. The glowy thing's a bomb!

1129
00:58:23.333 --> 00:58:25.335
[Mu]

1130
00:58:28.755 --> 00:58:31.091
Karen: There's a vehicle
approaching on your right.

1131
00:58:31.258 --> 00:58:33.468
Judge:
We have now entered sudden death.

1132
00:58:33.635 --> 00:58:36.430
The next correct answer wins
the championship.

1133
00:58:37.139 --> 00:58:38.140
[Grunts]

1134
00:58:40.767 --> 00:58:42.686
Judge: Midtown tech?

1135
00:58:42.853 --> 00:58:44.479
Zero.

1136
00:58:44.646 --> 00:58:45.689
That is correct.

1137
00:58:46.440 --> 00:58:48.734
Midtown takes the championship.

1138
00:58:48.942 --> 00:58:52.237
Flash: Woo-hoo! We won.
Liz: You guys. I am so proud of you.

1139
00:58:52.404 --> 00:58:55.574
Flash: Told you we didn't need Peter.
Ned: Flash. you didn't answer a question.

1140
00:58:55.741 --> 00:58:58.702
- Taking it all in. Michelle?
- Oh. yeah. I just. um...

1141
00:58:58.869 --> 00:59:01.269
I don't want to celebrate something
that was built by slaves.

1142
00:59:01.371 --> 00:59:03.832
I'm sure the Washington monument
wasn't built by—-

1143
00:59:04.041 --> 00:59:05.417
[mu]

1144
00:59:07.294 --> 00:59:08.336
Okay.

1145
00:59:08.795 --> 00:59:10.964
- Enjoy your book.
- Thanks.

1146
00:59:11.173 --> 00:59:13.383
[Yodeling ringtone plays]

1147
00:59:13.550 --> 00:59:16.011
- Oh. ned. you're alive.
- Peter. are you okay?

1148
00:59:16.178 --> 00:59:17.778
Where's the glowy thing?
The glowy thing?

1149
00:59:17.929 --> 00:59:21.516
- It's safe. It's in my backpack.
- Ned. listen. the glowy thing is dangerous.

1150
00:59:21.683 --> 00:59:23.403
You missed the decathlon.
I covered for you.

1151
00:59:23.435 --> 00:59:25.353
- Listen.
- We're at the Washington monument.

1152
00:59:25.520 --> 00:59:26.897
- Peter. is that you?
- Hey. Liz.

1153
00:59:27.064 --> 00:59:28.624
- Karen: Is that Liz?
- Put ned back on the phone.

1154
00:59:28.648 --> 00:59:31.777
- Karen: You should tell her how you feel.
- You flake. You are lucky we won.

1155
00:59:31.943 --> 00:59:35.530
I want to be mad. but I'm more worried.
Like. what is going on with you?

1156
00:59:35.697 --> 00:59:37.217
I have to talk to ned. It's important.

1157
00:59:37.365 --> 00:59:38.565
All items on the belt. please.

1158
00:59:38.700 --> 00:59:39.844
Peter:
There's something in ned's backpack.

1159
00:59:39.868 --> 00:59:41.870
It's dangerous.
Don't let it go through an X-ray.

1160
00:59:42.079 --> 00:59:43.789
[Crackling]

1161
00:59:44.790 --> 00:59:46.958
Liz? Liz! Damn it.

1162
00:59:47.167 --> 00:59:49.169
[Mu]

1163
00:59:50.462 --> 00:59:52.756
Can I be the one
to tell Peter he's expelled?

1164
00:59:52.964 --> 00:59:54.633
[Grunts]

1165
00:59:56.968 --> 01:00:02.724
The Washington monument is 555 feet.
five and one-eighth inches tall.

1166
01:00:02.933 --> 01:00:04.309
[Mu]

1167
01:00:04.476 --> 01:00:07.479
Notice how the marble and granite
are cut around the stone.

1168
01:00:14.903 --> 01:00:17.322
No. no. no.
Karen. what's going on up there?

1169
01:00:18.323 --> 01:00:19.923
Karen:
The chitauri core has detonated...

1170
01:00:19.991 --> 01:00:22.136
And caused severe structural damage
to the elevator.

1171
01:00:22.160 --> 01:00:23.513
- Oh. no.
- My friends are up there.

1172
01:00:23.537 --> 01:00:26.081
What? Uh. don't worry. ma'am.
everything's gonna be okay.

1173
01:00:26.248 --> 01:00:28.333
Excuse me. excuse me.
Oh. my god. that's tall.

1174
01:00:31.878 --> 01:00:33.964
[All gasping]

1175
01:00:34.422 --> 01:00:35.924
Oh. my god. Look at the ceiling.

1176
01:00:36.091 --> 01:00:37.592
Liz: Just stay calm. everyone.

1177
01:00:37.759 --> 01:00:39.427
Oh. we are all going to die here.

1178
01:00:42.055 --> 01:00:44.724
Karen: Estimating 10 minutes
before catastrophic failure.

1179
01:00:44.891 --> 01:00:46.393
We're freaking screwed.

1180
01:00:46.560 --> 01:00:49.688
Okay. I know that was scary.
but our safety systems are working.

1181
01:00:49.855 --> 01:00:52.274
Karen: The safety systems
are completely failing.

1182
01:00:52.440 --> 01:00:54.109
We're very safe in here.

1183
01:00:54.276 --> 01:00:56.862
Karen: The occupants are
in imminent mortal danger.

1184
01:00:57.028 --> 01:00:58.113
Going as fast as I can!

1185
01:00:59.948 --> 01:01:01.575
[All clamoring]

1186
01:01:07.831 --> 01:01:09.471
Man 1: Let's go.
Man 2: Give me your hand.

1187
01:01:10.584 --> 01:01:12.904
Karen: You now have 125 seconds
until catastrophic failure.

1188
01:01:13.044 --> 01:01:14.087
What?! Why?

1189
01:01:14.588 --> 01:01:17.591
Unexpected motion has caused
the deterioration to escalate.

1190
01:01:17.757 --> 01:01:21.219
- How do I get in there?
- Activating reconnaissance drone.

1191
01:01:21.928 --> 01:01:22.971
[Whistling]

1192
01:01:23.180 --> 01:01:25.974
Whoa. Has that been there
this whole time? That's awesome.

1193
01:01:26.433 --> 01:01:28.685
Locating optimal entry point.

1194
01:01:30.395 --> 01:01:32.063
Proceed to southwest window.

1195
01:01:32.230 --> 01:01:33.982
Karen. I'm on my way.

1196
01:01:38.528 --> 01:01:40.568
Liz: There's a lot of glass here.
Man: You got this.

1197
01:01:40.697 --> 01:01:41.907
Keep coming. keep coming.

1198
01:01:45.368 --> 01:01:46.995
[Mu]

1199
01:01:50.415 --> 01:01:52.125
[Groans]

1200
01:01:52.959 --> 01:01:54.753
[Wind whistling]

1201
01:01:55.962 --> 01:01:57.964
Okay. Oh. my god.

1202
01:01:58.131 --> 01:01:59.799
Okay.

1203
01:02:01.468 --> 01:02:03.654
Karen: What's wrong? You've reached
the southwest window.

1204
01:02:03.678 --> 01:02:05.430
- Why are you hesitating?
- It's fine.

1205
01:02:05.597 --> 01:02:07.307
I've just never been this high before.

1206
01:02:07.474 --> 01:02:09.643
You have also not reinstalled
your parachute...

1207
01:02:09.809 --> 01:02:12.520
So a fall from this height
would most likely be lethal.

1208
01:02:14.147 --> 01:02:15.607
Perfect.

1209
01:02:15.774 --> 01:02:17.359
Oh. my god.

1210
01:02:17.567 --> 01:02:18.693
[Grunts]

1211
01:02:18.902 --> 01:02:20.028
Why is it not breaking?

1212
01:02:20.195 --> 01:02:23.865
It's four-inch ballistic glass.
You'll have to create more momentum.

1213
01:02:43.093 --> 01:02:45.428
Officer 1: This is DC. Metro police.
Identify yourself.

1214
01:02:45.595 --> 01:02:47.180
Peter:
My friends are in there! Stop!

1215
01:02:47.347 --> 01:02:49.099
Return to the ground immediately.

1216
01:02:49.266 --> 01:02:51.268
- Okay. who's next?
- Flash: Me. it's my turn.

1217
01:02:51.434 --> 01:02:53.270
Ned:
Flash. seriously? What are you doing?

1218
01:02:53.436 --> 01:02:56.398
- Come on.
- Liz: Don't worry about the trophy.

1219
01:02:56.564 --> 01:02:58.108
[All yelling]

1220
01:03:03.863 --> 01:03:05.031
Officer 1: Stand down!

1221
01:03:05.198 --> 01:03:07.951
Return to the ground immediately.

1222
01:03:12.122 --> 01:03:14.124
Return to the ground
or we will open fire!

1223
01:03:14.291 --> 01:03:16.126
Officer 2: Go up. go up.

1224
01:03:16.960 --> 01:03:18.336
Peter: I got this.

1225
01:03:18.503 --> 01:03:20.171
Take my trophy.

1226
01:03:22.007 --> 01:03:24.217
Officer 1:
This is your last chance.

1227
01:03:24.384 --> 01:03:26.428
Peter: I'm gonna die.

1228
01:03:27.095 --> 01:03:28.555
Look out!

1229
01:03:36.938 --> 01:03:38.690
[All screaming]

1230
01:03:46.948 --> 01:03:48.783
[Grunting]

1231
01:04:05.592 --> 01:04:07.987
[In New York accent] Hey.
how you doing? Don't worry. I got you.

1232
01:04:08.011 --> 01:04:10.555
- Yes! Yes.
- Peter [in normal voice]: Hey. hey.

1233
01:04:10.722 --> 01:04:12.807
- Big guy. quit moving around.
- I'm sorry. sir.

1234
01:04:13.516 --> 01:04:15.393
[Sirens wailing]

1235
01:04:16.436 --> 01:04:17.479
Man: Let's go. let's go!

1236
01:04:23.360 --> 01:04:24.402
Okay. okay.

1237
01:04:24.569 --> 01:04:26.529
Liz: Mr. Harrington. go.
Harrington: Ned. come on.

1238
01:04:26.696 --> 01:04:28.490
- Peter: This is your stop.
- Come on. Liz.

1239
01:04:28.656 --> 01:04:31.576
Peter: Go. go. go. Everybody out.
Move it. people. Move it. move it.

1240
01:04:31.743 --> 01:04:33.503
Liz: Are you sure it's safe?
Harrington: Liz.

1241
01:04:34.162 --> 01:04:35.372
Peter: Liz!

1242
01:04:36.623 --> 01:04:38.083
[Liz screaming]

1243
01:04:39.584 --> 01:04:41.252
You're okay. You're okay.

1244
01:04:44.756 --> 01:04:46.132
Okay.

1245
01:04:46.674 --> 01:04:47.967
- Liz: Oh. my god.
- Good. good.

1246
01:04:48.134 --> 01:04:50.011
Come on up.
Come on. you guys. stay back.

1247
01:04:50.178 --> 01:04:52.180
Man 1:Come on in.
Man 2: You guys good?

1248
01:04:52.347 --> 01:04:53.947
[In New York accent]
So is everyone okay?

1249
01:04:55.183 --> 01:04:57.185
Karen:
This is your chance. Peter.

1250
01:04:57.352 --> 01:04:59.187
Kiss her.

1251
01:05:00.230 --> 01:05:01.439
[Clanging]

1252
01:05:02.941 --> 01:05:04.609
Thank you.

1253
01:05:07.612 --> 01:05:10.156
Are you really friends with Peter Parker?

1254
01:05:17.122 --> 01:05:22.001
I can finish the next order. but without
any new materials from that truck...

1255
01:05:22.585 --> 01:05:24.754
Yeah. damn it.

1256
01:05:25.255 --> 01:05:27.495
We still have enough to do
the gargan deal though. right?

1257
01:05:27.632 --> 01:05:29.634
Yeah. but then that's it.

1258
01:05:33.388 --> 01:05:35.849
Maybe it is time
that I built the high-altitude seal.

1259
01:05:36.015 --> 01:05:38.055
- Would you shut up about that?
- It's only one job.

1260
01:05:40.770 --> 01:05:44.023
Eight years. not a word from the feds.
nothing from those...

1261
01:05:44.190 --> 01:05:48.236
Halloween-costume-wearing bozos
up there in stark tower.

1262
01:05:48.403 --> 01:05:53.116
And then all of a sudden.
this little bastard in red tights shows up.

1263
01:05:53.283 --> 01:05:56.953
And he thinks he can tear down
everything I've built.

1264
01:05:58.455 --> 01:05:59.998
Really?

1265
01:06:01.166 --> 01:06:02.333
I'm gonna kill him.

1266
01:06:02.500 --> 01:06:04.544
- I'm gonna find him...
- I found him.

1267
01:06:04.711 --> 01:06:06.147
Reporter [on TV]:
The spider-man swooped in...

1268
01:06:06.171 --> 01:06:09.090
Heroically saving an academic
decathlon team from queens.

1269
01:06:09.757 --> 01:06:12.469
The identity of the masked hero
is still unknown.

1270
01:06:14.929 --> 01:06:17.474
- Mom.
- Woman: Oh. kids. All right.

1271
01:06:17.640 --> 01:06:20.143
Peter. Come here.
come here. come here.

1272
01:06:20.310 --> 01:06:22.312
[Mu]

1273
01:06:24.063 --> 01:06:26.566
This past weekend.
midtown's academic decathlon team...

1274
01:06:26.733 --> 01:06:29.694
Defeated the country's best
to win the national championship.

1275
01:06:29.861 --> 01:06:31.529
Later that day.
they also defeated death.

1276
01:06:31.696 --> 01:06:34.115
Explosion. Sally scream.
Flash scream. Everybody screaming.

1277
01:06:34.282 --> 01:06:38.077
There were purple lasers and smoke.
It was ♪♪♪♪ tight. like a bon jovi concert.

1278
01:06:38.244 --> 01:06:41.623
As you know. we made it out alive.
and that's the important thing.

1279
01:06:41.789 --> 01:06:44.876
I couldn't bear to lose
a student on a school trip.

1280
01:06:46.127 --> 01:06:47.170
Not again.

1281
01:06:47.337 --> 01:06:51.466
Thankfully. no one was seriously injured
thanks to the spider-man.

1282
01:06:51.674 --> 01:06:53.594
- Thank you. spider-man.
- Thank you. spider-man.

1283
01:06:53.635 --> 01:06:56.554
Jason: Up next: The spider-man mania
is sweeping the school.

1284
01:06:56.721 --> 01:06:59.349
How can you show your spider spirit?

1285
01:07:00.391 --> 01:07:02.101
[School bell ringing]

1286
01:07:03.269 --> 01:07:05.188
Dude. dude. dude.

1287
01:07:05.355 --> 01:07:08.066
What is it like being famous
when nobody knows it's you?

1288
01:07:08.233 --> 01:07:09.692
- Crazy. dude.
- It's crazy.

1289
01:07:09.859 --> 01:07:11.694
- Should we tell everyone?
- No.

1290
01:07:11.861 --> 01:07:14.656
- Should I tell everyone?
- No. dude. That's not a good idea.

1291
01:07:15.073 --> 01:07:18.159
- Okay. come on. we'll be late to class.
- I'm not going to class.

1292
01:07:18.326 --> 01:07:20.221
You're already in trouble
for ditching the decathlon.

1293
01:07:20.245 --> 01:07:21.788
Dude. listen. I figured it out.

1294
01:07:21.955 --> 01:07:23.875
The wingsuit guy is stealing
from damage control.

1295
01:07:24.040 --> 01:07:27.043
What he takes from damage control.
that's how he builds the weapons.

1296
01:07:27.210 --> 01:07:30.129
- So all I gotta do is catch him.
- But we have a Spanish quiz.

1297
01:07:30.296 --> 01:07:32.507
Ned. I'm probably never gonna
come back here.

1298
01:07:32.674 --> 01:07:35.718
Mr. Stark is moving
the avengers upstate...

1299
01:07:35.885 --> 01:07:37.845
- So when I bring this guy in...
- Dude.

1300
01:07:38.012 --> 01:07:39.931
You want to be a high school dropout?

1301
01:07:40.098 --> 01:07:42.767
I am so far beyond high school right now.

1302
01:07:42.934 --> 01:07:45.645
Parker. my office.

1303
01:07:50.108 --> 01:07:51.609
You got detention.

1304
01:07:51.776 --> 01:07:53.945
You screwed up.
You know what you did was wrong.

1305
01:07:54.112 --> 01:07:56.489
The question is.
how are you gonna make things right?

1306
01:07:56.656 --> 01:07:57.976
Maybe you were trying to be cool.

1307
01:07:58.533 --> 01:08:01.202
But take it from a guy
who's been frozen for 65 years...

1308
01:08:01.369 --> 01:08:04.497
The only way to really be cool
is to follow the rules.

1309
01:08:05.498 --> 01:08:08.126
We all know what's right.
We all know what's wrong.

1310
01:08:08.293 --> 01:08:10.837
Next time those turkeys try
to convince you of something...

1311
01:08:11.004 --> 01:08:13.256
- You know is wrong...
- Where you going? Get back here.

1312
01:08:13.423 --> 01:08:15.800
Just think to yourself.
what would captain america do?

1313
01:08:15.967 --> 01:08:17.760
Why are you here?
You don't have detention.

1314
01:08:17.927 --> 01:08:21.514
Oh. I know. I just like coming here
to sketch people in crisis.

1315
01:08:23.516 --> 01:08:24.517
[Chuckling]

1316
01:08:24.726 --> 01:08:26.269
It's you.

1317
01:08:26.769 --> 01:08:30.523
So your body's changing.
Believe me. I know how that feels.

1318
01:08:42.118 --> 01:08:43.786
May?

1319
01:08:47.290 --> 01:08:48.333
Hey. Karen. What's up?

1320
01:08:48.499 --> 01:08:50.293
Karen: Hey. Peter.
How was your Spanish quiz?

1321
01:08:50.460 --> 01:08:51.687
I was wondering if you could help me.

1322
01:08:51.711 --> 01:08:54.356
I'm trying to figure out who the guys
under the bridge were that night...

1323
01:08:54.380 --> 01:08:56.841
But I can only remember
part of a license plate.

1324
01:08:57.008 --> 01:08:59.802
I can run facial recognition
on the footage of that encounter.

1325
01:08:59.969 --> 01:09:01.471
- Footage?
- Yes. Peter.

1326
01:09:01.638 --> 01:09:03.514
I record everything you see.

1327
01:09:03.681 --> 01:09:04.807
- Everything?
- Everything.

1328
01:09:04.974 --> 01:09:07.310
- All the time?
- It's called the baby monitor protocol.

1329
01:09:08.102 --> 01:09:11.022
Yeah. of course it is. Um...

1330
01:09:11.230 --> 01:09:14.067
- Yeah. just roll it back to last Friday.
- With pleasure.

1331
01:09:14.233 --> 01:09:16.253
Peter [on video]:
Hey. everyone. Yeah. kick-ass party.

1332
01:09:16.277 --> 01:09:18.863
Hey. what's up. Liz?
Peter's told me a lot about you.

1333
01:09:19.030 --> 01:09:20.990
No. no. no.
This is just me messing around.

1334
01:09:21.157 --> 01:09:22.867
Go later in the day. later in the day.

1335
01:09:23.034 --> 01:09:25.203
Peter [in British accent]:
It is I. Thor. son of Odin.

1336
01:09:25.370 --> 01:09:26.829
No. no. no. That's definitely...

1337
01:09:26.996 --> 01:09:28.724
That's definitely not
what we wanted to watch.

1338
01:09:28.748 --> 01:09:32.251
- Karen: Your impressions are funny.
- Fast-fonnard to the arms deal.

1339
01:09:32.418 --> 01:09:33.711
Okay.

1340
01:09:33.878 --> 01:09:35.505
The two on the right. who are they?

1341
01:09:35.672 --> 01:09:37.432
Kare n:
Searching law-enforcement databases.

1342
01:09:38.257 --> 01:09:40.259
No records found
for two of the individuals.

1343
01:09:40.426 --> 01:09:42.512
- Nothing?
- Karen: One individual identified.

1344
01:09:42.679 --> 01:09:44.806
Aaron Davis. age 33.

1345
01:09:44.972 --> 01:09:47.809
He has a criminal record
and an address here in queens.

1346
01:09:47.975 --> 01:09:49.227
Let's pay him a visit.

1347
01:09:49.394 --> 01:09:52.730
Karen: Would you like me to activate
the enhanced interrogation protocol?

1348
01:09:52.897 --> 01:09:53.981
Uh. yeah.

1349
01:10:09.205 --> 01:10:10.957
- [In deep voice] Remember me?
- Hey...

1350
01:10:11.124 --> 01:10:12.959
I need information.
You'll give it to me now.

1351
01:10:13.126 --> 01:10:14.836
- All right. chill.
- Come on!

1352
01:10:15.586 --> 01:10:18.214
- What happened to your voice?
- What do you mean?

1353
01:10:18.381 --> 01:10:20.609
I heard you by the bridge.
I know what a girl sound like.

1354
01:10:20.633 --> 01:10:23.594
I'm not a girl. I'm a boy.
I mean. I'm a... I'm a man.

1355
01:10:23.761 --> 01:10:25.596
I don't care what you are. a boy. a girl...

1356
01:10:25.763 --> 01:10:27.432
I'm not a girl. I'm a man.

1357
01:10:27.598 --> 01:10:29.934
Come on. man.
Look. who is selling these weapons?

1358
01:10:30.309 --> 01:10:32.395
I need to know. Give me names or else.

1359
01:10:36.065 --> 01:10:40.361
- You ain't ever done this before. huh?
- Deactivate interrogation mode.

1360
01:10:41.738 --> 01:10:42.858
[In normal voice] Look. man.

1361
01:10:43.448 --> 01:10:46.159
These guys are selling weapons
that are crazy dangerous.

1362
01:10:46.325 --> 01:10:47.744
They can't be out on the streets.

1363
01:10:47.910 --> 01:10:50.079
If one of them can cut
delmar's bodega in half...

1364
01:10:50.246 --> 01:10:52.832
- You know delmar's?
- Yeah. best sandwich in queens.

1365
01:10:52.999 --> 01:10:55.209
- Sub haven's pretty good.
- Eh. it's too much bread.

1366
01:10:55.376 --> 01:10:57.503
- I like bread.
- Come on. man. please.

1367
01:10:59.839 --> 01:11:02.550
Stupid interrogation mode.
Karen. don't ever do that again.

1368
01:11:02.717 --> 01:11:06.179
The other night. you told that dude.
"if you shoot somebody. shoot me."

1369
01:11:06.345 --> 01:11:07.805
It's pretty ballsy.

1370
01:11:07.972 --> 01:11:10.016
I don't want those weapons
in this neighborhood.

1371
01:11:10.183 --> 01:11:11.559
I got a nephew who live here.

1372
01:11:12.769 --> 01:11:14.020
Who are these guys?

1373
01:11:14.187 --> 01:11:16.147
What can you tell me
about the guy with the wings?

1374
01:11:16.272 --> 01:11:18.592
Other than he's a psychopath
dressed like a demon. nothing.

1375
01:11:18.691 --> 01:11:20.651
I don't know who he is
or where he is.

1376
01:11:21.944 --> 01:11:23.404
[Peter sighs]

1377
01:11:23.571 --> 01:11:27.116
- I do know where he's gonna be.
- Really?

1378
01:11:27.283 --> 01:11:29.535
Yeah. this crazy dude
I used to work with...

1379
01:11:29.702 --> 01:11:32.121
He's supposed
to be doing a deal with him.

1380
01:11:32.288 --> 01:11:33.915
Yes! Yes.

1381
01:11:34.081 --> 01:11:35.666
- Thank...
- Hey. Hey. Hey.

1382
01:11:35.833 --> 01:11:38.127
I didn't tell you where.
You don't have a location.

1383
01:11:38.294 --> 01:11:40.797
Right. of course.
Yeah. my bad. Silly. Just...

1384
01:11:42.381 --> 01:11:44.550
- Where is it?
- Can I give you some advice?

1385
01:11:44.759 --> 01:11:47.762
- Hmm?
- You gotta get better at this part of the job.

1386
01:11:47.929 --> 01:11:49.388
I don't understand.

1387
01:11:49.555 --> 01:11:50.932
I'm intimidating.

1388
01:11:51.098 --> 01:11:53.976
- Staten island ferry. 11.
- Oh. that's soon.

1389
01:11:54.143 --> 01:11:55.853
That's gonna dissolve in two hours.

1390
01:11:56.020 --> 01:11:58.606
No. no. no. Come fix this.

1391
01:11:58.773 --> 01:12:00.584
- Two hours. You deserve that.
- I got ice cream in here.

1392
01:12:00.608 --> 01:12:03.194
You deserve that. You're a criminal.
Bye. Mr. Criminal.

1393
01:12:14.747 --> 01:12:16.749
[Grunting]

1394
01:12:17.834 --> 01:12:19.126
Nice.

1395
01:12:22.421 --> 01:12:25.049
Okay. Karen. activate
enhanced reconnaissance mode.

1396
01:12:25.216 --> 01:12:26.259
Kare n: Sure thing.

1397
01:12:26.634 --> 01:12:28.761
Toomes:
He's up front. main deck.

1398
01:12:28.928 --> 01:12:30.346
I hate this guy.

1399
01:12:30.513 --> 01:12:32.849
It's the guy from the bridge. right?
Who's that other guy?

1400
01:12:33.015 --> 01:12:34.642
Toomes: Just keep me posted.

1401
01:12:34.809 --> 01:12:36.829
Karen: There's no record of him
in my criminal database.

1402
01:12:36.853 --> 01:12:39.665
Incoming call from may Parker. Should
lreroute to your heads-up display?

1403
01:12:39.689 --> 01:12:42.108
I can't talk right now. I'll call her back.

1404
01:12:42.984 --> 01:12:47.363
Hey. dronie. keep an eye on that guy.
We can't let anybody get away this time.

1405
01:12:55.621 --> 01:12:57.707
Peter: Who's the guy on the left?
Karen: Mac gargan.

1406
01:12:57.874 --> 01:13:00.293
Extensive criminal record.
including homicide.

1407
01:13:00.459 --> 01:13:02.295
Would you like me
to activate instant kill?

1408
01:13:02.461 --> 01:13:05.882
No. Karen. stop it
with the instant kill already.

1409
01:13:07.091 --> 01:13:09.385
White pickup truck.

1410
01:13:13.723 --> 01:13:16.017
Dronie. scan the ship
for a white pickup truck.

1411
01:13:36.913 --> 01:13:38.164
Oh. this is too perfect.

1412
01:13:38.331 --> 01:13:40.666
I got the weapons. buyers
and sellers in one place.

1413
01:13:40.833 --> 01:13:43.794
- Karen: Incoming call from Tony stark.
- No. no. no.

1414
01:13:43.961 --> 01:13:46.130
- Don't answer.
- Mr. Parker. Got a sec?

1415
01:13:46.297 --> 01:13:48.716
- Uh. I'm actually at school.
- Karen: No. you're not.

1416
01:13:48.883 --> 01:13:50.760
- Nice work in d. C.
- Okay.

1417
01:13:50.927 --> 01:13:53.638
My dad never really gave me
a lot of support...

1418
01:13:53.804 --> 01:13:55.973
And I'm trying to break
the cycle of shame.

1419
01:13:56.140 --> 01:13:57.451
Uh. I'm in the middle of something.

1420
01:13:57.475 --> 01:13:58.994
Don't cut me off
when I'm complimenting you.

1421
01:13:59.018 --> 01:14:00.645
Anyway. great things are about to...

1422
01:14:00.853 --> 01:14:02.146
[Ferry horn blaring]

1423
01:14:02.355 --> 01:14:04.774
- Tony: What is that?
- Uh. I'm at band practice.

1424
01:14:04.941 --> 01:14:09.612
That's odd. Happy told me you quit
band six weeks ago. What's up?

1425
01:14:09.779 --> 01:14:11.989
- I gotta go. Uh. end call.
- Hey.

1426
01:14:16.911 --> 01:14:20.247
Hey. guys. The illegal-weapons-deal ferry
was at 10:30. You missed it.

1427
01:14:20.456 --> 01:14:22.458
[All grunting]

1428
01:14:29.256 --> 01:14:30.883
Man: Spider guy's here.

1429
01:14:33.552 --> 01:14:36.055
Whoa. whoa. whoa. Not so fast.

1430
01:14:36.889 --> 01:14:40.184
Are you guys okay?
My bad. That was a little hard.

1431
01:14:40.726 --> 01:14:43.896
I got to say. the other guy was way better
with that thing.

1432
01:14:44.355 --> 01:14:45.564
I'm honestly...

1433
01:14:45.731 --> 01:14:47.692
I'm... I'm shocked.

1434
01:14:47.858 --> 01:14:49.235
[Man yelling]

1435
01:14:59.745 --> 01:15:01.706
- Man 1: Freeze! FBI.
- Don't move.

1436
01:15:01.872 --> 01:15:03.666
Man 1: Get on the ground.
Man 2: FBI.

1437
01:15:03.833 --> 01:15:04.875
What do you mean. FBI?

1438
01:15:05.042 --> 01:15:08.462
- Karen: Federal Bureau of Investigation.
- I know. but what are they doing here?

1439
01:15:09.880 --> 01:15:11.298
[Mu]

1440
01:15:16.429 --> 01:15:18.514
Get out of the way. Get out of the way!

1441
01:15:18.723 --> 01:15:20.808
Whoa. whoa. whoa! No.

1442
01:15:22.727 --> 01:15:25.521
Look out. look out. look out.
Move. move. move!

1443
01:15:31.152 --> 01:15:32.632
- Move.
- Toomes: Get to the top deck.

1444
01:15:32.695 --> 01:15:34.238
We're getting out of here.

1445
01:16:13.319 --> 01:16:15.404
Activate taser web!

1446
01:16:26.832 --> 01:16:29.877
You're messing with things
you don't understand.

1447
01:16:41.013 --> 01:16:42.765
[All screaming]

1448
01:17:09.250 --> 01:17:11.043
Oh. my god. What do I do? Karen...

1449
01:17:11.210 --> 01:17:14.463
Give me an X-ray of the boat
and target all the strongest points.

1450
01:17:17.299 --> 01:17:19.343
Web grenade. Web grenade.

1451
01:17:21.178 --> 01:17:23.389
Splitter web. go.

1452
01:17:23.556 --> 01:17:25.558
[Grunting]

1453
01:17:42.074 --> 01:17:44.076
[Panting]

1454
01:17:51.458 --> 01:17:54.587
Karen: Great job. Peter.
You are 98 percent successful.

1455
01:17:54.753 --> 01:17:58.007
- Ninety—eight?
- Yeah. spider-man!

1456
01:17:59.175 --> 01:18:01.760
No. no. no.

1457
01:18:07.641 --> 01:18:09.393
[Car alarm blares then fizzles]

1458
01:18:11.478 --> 01:18:13.397
[All shouting]

1459
01:18:25.201 --> 01:18:26.493
