01:56:28.773 --> 01:56:30.817
I thought you didn't have any friends.

1965
01:56:30.984 --> 01:56:32.903
I didn't.

1966
01:56:33.570 --> 01:56:35.030
[Cell phone buzzes]

1967
01:56:37.782 --> 01:56:39.784
- I. uh. gotta go.
- Hey. where you going?

1968
01:56:42.496 --> 01:56:44.623
What are you hiding. Peter?

1969
01:56:46.917 --> 01:56:48.502
I'm just kidding. I don't care. Bye.

1970
01:56:48.668 --> 01:56:51.338
- All right. so we should run some drills.
- Ned: Yeah.

1971
01:56:59.763 --> 01:57:03.099
Hey. happy. What. uh...?
What are you doing here?

1972
01:57:04.059 --> 01:57:05.310
I really owe you one.

1973
01:57:07.395 --> 01:57:09.689
I don't know what I would do
without this job.

1974
01:57:09.856 --> 01:57:11.650
I mean. before I met Tony...

1975
01:57:11.816 --> 01:57:13.568
[Toilet flushes]

1976
01:57:41.471 --> 01:57:43.473
So. uh. how long you been here?

1977
01:57:43.640 --> 01:57:45.809
Long enough to be awkward.
Boss wants to see you.

1978
01:57:46.768 --> 01:57:49.646
- [Whispers] Is he here too?
- In the toilet? No. he's upstate.

1979
01:57:50.188 --> 01:57:51.832
[In normal voice]
Upstate... like. "upstate" upstate?

1980
01:57:51.856 --> 01:57:53.441
Yeah. let's go.

1981
01:57:54.818 --> 01:57:55.944
Take a look.

1982
01:57:56.111 --> 01:57:58.154
It's pretty impressive. huh?

1983
01:57:59.239 --> 01:58:01.992
They just finished remodeling
the whole thing.

1984
01:58:04.619 --> 01:58:05.954
[Mu]

1985
01:58:28.226 --> 01:58:31.271
- You don't see that every day.
- Oh. there they are.

1986
01:58:31.938 --> 01:58:33.565
How was the ride up?

1987
01:58:33.982 --> 01:58:36.610
- Good.
- Give me a minute with the kid.

1988
01:58:37.360 --> 01:58:39.195
- Seriously?
- Yeah.

1989
01:58:39.613 --> 01:58:40.989
I gotta talk to the kid.

1990
01:58:41.573 --> 01:58:42.657
I'll be close behind.

1991
01:58:42.824 --> 01:58:46.578
How about a loose follow?
All right? Boundaries are good.

1992
01:58:51.583 --> 01:58:52.792
Sorry I took your suit.

1993
01:58:52.959 --> 01:58:55.462
You had it coming.
Actually. it turns out it was...

1994
01:58:55.629 --> 01:58:57.631
The perfect tough-love moment
that you needed.

1995
01:58:57.797 --> 01:59:00.634
To urge you on. right?
Wouldn't you think? Don't you think?

1996
01:59:00.800 --> 01:59:02.594
- I guess.
- Let's just say it was.

1997
01:59:03.136 --> 01:59:04.262
[Sighs]

1998
01:59:04.471 --> 01:59:07.682
- Mr. Stark. I really...
- You screwed the pooch hard. bigtime.

1999
01:59:08.308 --> 01:59:09.976
But then you did the right thing.

2000
01:59:10.143 --> 01:59:13.313
Took the dog to the free clinic.
you raised the hybrid puppies...

2001
01:59:13.480 --> 01:59:15.357
All right. not my best analogy.

2002
01:59:16.566 --> 01:59:18.485
I was wrong about you.

2003
01:59:19.027 --> 01:59:21.279
I think. with a little more mentoring...

2004
01:59:21.446 --> 01:59:23.907
You could be a real asset to the team.

2005
01:59:25.700 --> 01:59:27.535
- To the...? To the team?
- Yeah. Anyway...

2006
01:59:27.702 --> 01:59:30.747
There's about 50 reporters behind
that door. Real ones. not bloggers.

2007
01:59:31.247 --> 01:59:33.083
When you're ready...

2008
01:59:33.458 --> 01:59:35.168
Why don't you try that on?

2009
01:59:35.335 --> 01:59:39.255
And I'll introduce the world to the newest
official member of the avengers:

2010
01:59:39.422 --> 01:59:41.091
Spider-man.

2011
01:59:44.761 --> 01:59:46.054
[Chuckling]

2012
01:59:46.805 --> 01:59:49.057
Tony: Yeah. give that a look.

2013
01:59:54.562 --> 01:59:56.874
After the press conference.
happy will show you to your room...

2014
01:59:56.898 --> 01:59:57.982
Your new quarters.

2015
01:59:58.149 --> 02:00:00.402
Where's he between?
He's next to vision?

2016
02:00:00.568 --> 02:00:02.821
- Yeah. vision's not big on doors.
- It's fun.

2017
02:00:02.987 --> 02:00:04.322
Or walls.

2018
02:00:04.489 --> 02:00:06.366
You'll fit right in.

2019
02:00:12.789 --> 02:00:14.791
Thank you. Mr. Stark.

2020
02:00:15.250 --> 02:00:16.501
But I'm good.

2021
02:00:17.544 --> 02:00:20.046
You're good? Good...?
How are you good?

2022
02:00:20.213 --> 02:00:24.384
Well. I mean. I'd rather just stay
on the ground for a little while.

2023
02:00:24.551 --> 02:00:26.720
Friendly neighborhood spider-man.

2024
02:00:26.886 --> 02:00:28.966
Somebody's got to look out
for the little guy. right?

2025
02:00:29.305 --> 02:00:30.765
You're turning me down?

2026
02:00:30.932 --> 02:00:33.017
You better think about this.
Look at that.

2027
02:00:33.184 --> 02:00:34.436
Look at me.

2028
02:00:35.186 --> 02:00:36.271
Last chance. Yes or no?

2029
02:00:36.438 --> 02:00:37.731
-Okay.

2030
02:00:37.897 --> 02:00:41.401
It's kind of a Springsteen-y.
working-class hero vibe that I dig.

2031
02:00:41.568 --> 02:00:43.570
Uh. happy will take you home.

2032
02:00:43.737 --> 02:00:45.238
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

2033
02:00:45.405 --> 02:00:47.574
Mind waiting in the car?
I need a minute.

2034
02:00:49.117 --> 02:00:51.786
- Thank you. Mr. Stark.
- Yes. Mr. Parker. very well.

2035
02:00:51.953 --> 02:00:53.663
- See you around.
- Okay.

2036
02:01:01.880 --> 02:01:03.089
That was a test. right?

2037
02:01:03.882 --> 02:01:06.342
- There's nobody back there?
- Yes. you passed.

2038
02:01:07.218 --> 02:01:10.096
- All right. skedaddle there. young buck.
- Thank you. Mr. Stark.

2039
02:01:10.263 --> 02:01:11.973
Tony: Yeah. thank you.

2040
02:01:14.058 --> 02:01:15.935
Told you he's a good kid.

2041
02:01:20.190 --> 02:01:21.983
[Reporters chattering
indistinctly]

2042
02:01:22.192 --> 02:01:23.651
- Where's the kid?
- He left.

2043
02:01:23.818 --> 02:01:26.738
- Everybody's waiting.
- He actually made a mature choice.

2044
02:01:26.905 --> 02:01:29.908
- It just surprised the heck out of us.
- Did you screw this up?

2045
02:01:30.074 --> 02:01:32.303
- He told the kid to go wait in the car.
- Are you kidding?

2046
02:01:32.327 --> 02:01:34.496
I have a room full of people
in there waiting...

2047
02:01:34.662 --> 02:01:36.599
For some big announcement.
What will I tell them?

2048
02:01:36.623 --> 02:01:39.125
Think of something. How about. um...?

2049
02:01:39.667 --> 02:01:41.836
- Hap. you still got that ring?
- Do I...? I...?

2050
02:01:42.003 --> 02:01:43.314
- The engagement ring.
- Are you kidding?

2051
02:01:43.338 --> 02:01:46.549
I've been carrying this since 2008.

2052
02:01:49.219 --> 02:01:50.345
Okay.

2053
02:01:50.512 --> 02:01:52.239
I think I can think
of something better than that.

2054
02:01:52.263 --> 02:01:54.641
Well. it would buy us a little time.

2055
02:01:55.934 --> 02:01:58.061
Like we need time.

2056
02:01:58.228 --> 02:02:00.039
Pepper: I can't believe you have that
in your pocket.

2057
02:02:00.063 --> 02:02:02.565
- Want me to get the door for you. hon?
- I got it.

